-- Peru Stocks: Intergroup, Luna Gold, Rio Alto, Trevali
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-07-19T21:08:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-19/peru-stocks-intercorp-financial-trevali-mining-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trade in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.1 percent to 20,115.50. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 0.2 percent to 2,703.90.  Trevali Mining Corp. (TV)  , a Canadian zinc and silver
producer with operations in Peru, rose 3.8 percent to 82 cents.
The shares gained as zinc climbed in London, said  Daniel Romero ,
an analyst at Lima-based investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner,
gained for the fourth day in five, adding 2.1 percent to $4.32
as gold advanced in New York.  Luna Gold Corp. (LGC)  , a Canadian gold explorer, rose
2.1 percent to $1.96.  Intergroup Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , the owner of
Peru’s fourth-largest bank, gained for a third straight session,
adding 1 percent to $31.50. Total  car loans  jumped 20 percent in
June from a year earlier and the country’s bad-loans ratio was
unchanged, according to the Peruvian Banking Association.
Intergroup is due to report earnings July 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
